Adminer for Oracle DB

credits:https://blog.shellnetsecurity.com/2022/09/337/general/configuring-adminer-for-oracle-databases/


Access an Oracle Database From adminer
Oracle database conencts via TNS Name. 

environment variable TNS_ADMIN to the path of /usr/local/oracle/instantclient_21_7/network/admin. 

You need create a tnsnames.ora file to be used for my connection to Oracle database. 
For those that aren’t familiar with tnsnames.ora and its syntax, you should read up on them in Oracle’s documentation.
https://docs.oracle.com/en/database/oracle/oracle-database/21/netrf/local-naming-parameters-in-tns-ora-file.html#GUID-7F967CE5-5498-427C-9390-4A5C6767ADAA


Sample:

oracle_rds = (DESCRIPTION=(ADDRESS=(PROTOCOL=TCP)(HOST=oracle-rds.amazon.com)(PORT=1521))(CONNECT_DATA=(SID=ORCL)))
